{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1240,"text":"I come from Lebanon,"},{"time":4140,"text":"and I believe that running\ncan change the world."},{"time":8080,"text":"I know what I have just said\nis simply not obvious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":12240,"text":"You know, Lebanon as a country\nhas been once destroyed"},{"time":17110,"text":"by a long and bloody civil war."},{"time":20100,"text":"Honestly, I don't know\nwhy they call it civil war"},{"time":23200,"text":"when there is nothing civil about it."},{"time":26180,"text":"With Syria to the north,\nIsrael and Palestine to the south,"},{"time":31180,"text":"and our government\neven up till this moment"},{"time":34240,"text":"is still fragmented and unstable."},{"time":38140,"text":"For years, the country has been divided\nbetween politics and religion."},{"time":45070,"text":"However, for one day a year,"},{"time":48100,"text":"we truly stand united,"},{"time":50240,"text":"and that's when the marathon takes place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55050,"text":"I used to be a marathon runner."},{"time":58170,"text":"Long distance running\nwas not only good for my well-being"},{"time":63050,"text":"but it helped me meditate and dream big."},{"time":67210,"text":"So the longer distances I ran,"},{"time":70070,"text":"the bigger my dreams became."},{"time":73050,"text":"Until one fateful morning,"},{"time":76090,"text":"and while training, I was hit by a bus."},{"time":82160,"text":"I nearly died, was in a coma,"},{"time":85240,"text":"stayed at the hospital for two years,"},{"time":89030,"text":"and underwent 36 surgeries\nto be able to walk again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95240,"text":"As soon as I came out of my coma,"},{"time":98150,"text":"I realized that I was no longer\nthe same runner I used to be,"},{"time":103190,"text":"so I decided, if I couldn't run myself,"},{"time":107240,"text":"I wanted to make sure that others could."},{"time":112040,"text":"So out of my hospital bed,"},{"time":114090,"text":"I asked my husband to start taking notes,"},{"time":117090,"text":"and a few months later,\nthe marathon was born."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123240,"text":"Organizing a marathon\nas a reaction to an accident"},{"time":127240,"text":"may sound strange,"},{"time":130150,"text":"but at that time, even during\nmy most vulnerable condition,"},{"time":135130,"text":"I needed to dream big."},{"time":137130,"text":"I needed something\nto take me out of my pain,"},{"time":140120,"text":"an objective to look forward to."},{"time":143180,"text":"I didn't want to pity myself,\nnor to be pitied,"},{"time":148050,"text":"and I thought by organizing\nsuch a marathon,"},{"time":151170,"text":"I'll be able to pay back to my community,"},{"time":154170,"text":"build bridges with the outside world,"},{"time":157070,"text":"and invite runners to come to Lebanon"},{"time":159240,"text":"and run under the umbrella of peace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":164240,"text":"Organizing a marathon in Lebanon"},{"time":167100,"text":"is definitely not like organizing\none in New York."},{"time":172180,"text":"How do you introduce\nthe concept of running"},{"time":175140,"text":"to a nation that is constantly\nat the brink of war?"},{"time":180200,"text":"How do you ask those\nwho were once fighting"},{"time":183170,"text":"and killing each other"},{"time":185170,"text":"to come together and run\nnext to each other?"},{"time":189150,"text":"More than that, how do you convince people\nto run a distance of 26.2 miles"},{"time":196080,"text":"at a time they were not even familiar\nwith the word \"marathon\"?"},{"time":201140,"text":"So we had to start from scratch."}]},{"cues":[{"time":203240,"text":"For almost two years,\nwe went all over the country"},{"time":207190,"text":"and even visited remote villages."},{"time":211140,"text":"I personally met with people\nfrom all walks of life --"},{"time":215220,"text":"mayors, NGOs, schoolchildren,"},{"time":218240,"text":"politicians, militiamen,"},{"time":222010,"text":"people from mosques, churches,"},{"time":224240,"text":"the president of the country,\neven housewives."},{"time":229130,"text":"I learned one thing:"},{"time":232070,"text":"When you walk the talk,\npeople believe you."},{"time":236180,"text":"Many were touched by my personal story,"},{"time":240180,"text":"and they shared their stories in return."},{"time":243240,"text":"It was honesty and transparency\nthat brought us together."},{"time":249070,"text":"We spoke one common language\nto each other,"},{"time":252240,"text":"and that was from one human to another."},{"time":257190,"text":"Once that trust was built,"},{"time":260050,"text":"everybody wanted\nto be part of the marathon"},{"time":263020,"text":"to show the world the true colors\nof Lebanon and the Lebanese"},{"time":268150,"text":"and their desire to live\nin peace and harmony."}]},{"cues":[{"time":273150,"text":"In October 2003, over 6,000 runners"},{"time":278150,"text":"from 49 different nationalities"},{"time":281040,"text":"came to the start line, all determined,"},{"time":285020,"text":"and when the gunfire went off,"},{"time":287190,"text":"this time it was a signal\nto run in harmony,"},{"time":292190,"text":"for a change."}]},{"cues":[{"time":294240,"text":"The marathon grew."},{"time":296230,"text":"So did our political problems."},{"time":299240,"text":"But for every disaster we had,"},{"time":302170,"text":"the marathon found ways\nto bring people together."},{"time":308110,"text":"In 2005, our prime minister\nwas assassinated,"},{"time":313030,"text":"and the country came\nto a complete standstill,"},{"time":317080,"text":"so we organized a five-kilometer\nUnited We Run campaign."},{"time":321240,"text":"Over 60,000 people came to the start line,"},{"time":325170,"text":"all wearing white T-shirts\nwith no political slogans."},{"time":331120,"text":"That was a turning point for the marathon,"},{"time":334100,"text":"where people started\nlooking at it as a platform"},{"time":338010,"text":"for peace and unity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340190,"text":"Between 2006 up to 2009,\nour country, Lebanon,"},{"time":345240,"text":"went through unstable years,"},{"time":348170,"text":"invasions, and more assassinations"},{"time":351200,"text":"that brought us close to a civil war."},{"time":354100,"text":"The country was divided again,"},{"time":356210,"text":"so much that our parliament resigned,"},{"time":360060,"text":"we had no president for a year,\nand no prime minister."},{"time":365060,"text":"But we did have a marathon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":368200,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":375060,"text":"So through the marathon, we learned\nthat political problems can be overcome."},{"time":382020,"text":"When the opposition party decided\nto shut down part of the city center,"},{"time":386240,"text":"we negotiated alternative routes."},{"time":390150,"text":"Government protesters\nbecame sideline cheerleaders."},{"time":394220,"text":"They even hosted juice stations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":397110,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":399230,"text":"You know, the marathon\nhas really become one of its kind."},{"time":405010,"text":"It gained credibility"},{"time":406220,"text":"from both the Lebanese\nand the international community."},{"time":412040,"text":"Last November 2012, over 33,000 runners\nfrom 85 different nationalities"},{"time":418240,"text":"came to the start line,"},{"time":420140,"text":"but this time, they challenged\na very stormy and rainy weather."},{"time":425180,"text":"The streets were flooded,\nbut people didn't want to miss out"},{"time":429180,"text":"on the opportunity of being part\nof such a national day."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435040,"text":"BMA has expanded."},{"time":436190,"text":"We include everyone:\nthe young, the elderly,"},{"time":440160,"text":"the disabled, the mentally challenged,"},{"time":443160,"text":"the blind, the elite, the amateur runners,"},{"time":447030,"text":"even moms with their babies."},{"time":449240,"text":"Themes have included\nruns for the environment,"},{"time":453090,"text":"breast cancer, for the love\nof Lebanon, for peace,"},{"time":457000,"text":"or just simply to run."}]},{"cues":[{"time":460030,"text":"The first annual all-women-and-girls\nrace for empowerment,"},{"time":466140,"text":"which is one of its kind in the region,"},{"time":468240,"text":"has just taken place only a few weeks ago,"},{"time":472100,"text":"with 4,512 women,\nincluding the first lady,"},{"time":477210,"text":"and this is only the beginning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481230,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483230,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":487120,"text":"BMA has supported charities and volunteers"},{"time":492030,"text":"who have helped reshape Lebanon,"},{"time":495050,"text":"raising funds for their causes"},{"time":497170,"text":"and encouraging others to give."},{"time":500220,"text":"The culture of giving and doing good\nhas become contagious."},{"time":505110,"text":"Stereotypes have been broken."},{"time":507190,"text":"Change-makers and future leaders\nhave been created."},{"time":512130,"text":"I believe these are the building blocks\nfor future peace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":519040,"text":"BMA has become such a respected\nevent in the region"},{"time":525190,"text":"that government officials in the region,"},{"time":528130,"text":"like Iraq, Egypt and Syria,"},{"time":531120,"text":"have asked the organization to help them\nstructure a similar sporting event."},{"time":538030,"text":"We are now one of the largest\nrunning events in the Middle East,"},{"time":542120,"text":"but most importantly,"},{"time":544120,"text":"it is a platform for hope and cooperation"},{"time":548240,"text":"in an ever-fragile\nand unstable part of the world."},{"time":554210,"text":"From Boston to Beirut, we stand as one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":560050,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":565240,"text":"After 10 years in Lebanon,"},{"time":567230,"text":"from national marathons\nor from national events"},{"time":571150,"text":"to smaller regional races,"},{"time":573220,"text":"we've seen that people want\nto run for a better future."},{"time":579110,"text":"After all, peacemaking is not a sprint."},{"time":585070,"text":"It is more of a marathon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587120,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588130,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}